Modifications
-------------

This fork has been adapted for the homelab use case and differs from
the upstream chart in the following material ways:

* Reworked backup/recovery to use the `barman-cloud.cloudnative-pg.io`
  CNPG plugin and a `barmancloud.cnpg.io/v1` `ObjectStore` CR
  (`templates/objectstore.yaml`) instead of the in-tree
  `backup.barmanObjectStore` cluster spec.
* Removed support for cluster types other than `postgresql`
  (PostGIS and TimescaleDB image/extension wiring removed).
* Removed `recovery.method: import` and the associated external
  cluster source.
* Removed `ImageCatalog` / `ClusterImageCatalog` integration.
* Removed managed `Database` CR generation
  (`templates/databases.yaml`).
* Removed CNPG Console StatefulSet
  (`templates/console-statefulset.yaml`).
* Removed in-chart credential `Secret` generation for backup, origin
  and recovery providers; secrets are expected to be provisioned
  out-of-band (e.g. by an OBC) and referenced by name.
* Restricted backup/recovery storage to S3-compatible providers;
  Azure Blob and GCS provider blocks were removed.
* Removed `helm test` resources (`templates/tests/`).
* Renamed the chart from `cluster` to `cnpg-cluster`, reset the chart
  version to `0.1.0`, and refreshed `Chart.yaml` metadata.

